The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in Ogun State has said a passerby was killed in an accident that involved three vehicles and six persons at the Toll Gate on the Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway. The Sector Commander, Mr Ahmed Umar, said five others were unhurt in the accident which occurred at about 10 pm on Saturday. BoT appeals to Kwarans to save central mosque from degradation ASUU strike: NLC to stage nationwide solidarity protest He said, “The corpse of the victim has been deposited at the morgue of the general hospital, Ifo.” Umar attributed the accident to mechanical deficiency, speeding and brake failure.(NAN)